      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "Good — I have the full picture from the past sessions. Here's exactly where things stand and what you can do right now.\n\n## Current state of Nostalgia d'Italia\n\n**Done and live:**\n- Static HTML portal live at `https://nostalgia-ditalia.netlify.app`\n- Sanity project `wdcy2hfs` (dataset: `production`) — all 33 documents published, all 11 asset cards patched with metadata\n- Sanity Studio live at the hosted URL\n- Full build guide written with security hardening (exact version pins, `.npmrc`, Socket Firewall)\n\n**Blocked:**\n- Schema corruption in Sanity — `assetCard` type has a duplicate `media` field from a double-deployment. Every `deploy_schema` call fails until you run one local CLI command. The `designTokens` and `referenceFile` types can't be deployed until this is fixed.\n- Next.js frontend not built — the static HTML is live but not connected to Sanity. No dynamic content yet.\n\n---\n\n## What you can do right now, today\n\n**In order of what unblocks the most:**\n\n**1. Fix the schema corruption — one command, five minutes.**\nThis is the thing holding everything else up. Run this locally:\n\n```bash\nnpx sanity@latest schema delete --project wdcy2hfs --dataset production --workspace default\n```\n\nThis does **not** touch your content documents — all 33 published documents survive. It only clears the corrupt schema definition. After running it, I can redeploy the schema cleanly via the Sanity MCP and unblock `designTokens` and `referenceFile`.\n\n**2. After that — I can via Sanity MCP right now:**\n- Redeploy the corrected schema\n- Add any new content types Jemima needs (food heritage sections, product listings, podcast episodes based on what emerged at the Odoo Birmingham show)\n- Audit current document states and patch anything missing\n\n**3. The Next.js frontend — your two real options:**\n\nOption A: you now have Netlify MCP connected. Last time it kept failing OAuth. Want to try it again right now? If it connects, I can attempt to scaffold the Next.js build from here using Netlify's agent.\n\nOption B: the fastest route given previous OAuth failures — I write the complete Next.js app as files you download and push to GitHub, then Netlify auto-deploys from the repo. Given you have the AGENTS.md setup now and Qwen/Gemma on OCI, you could also run it locally via Claude Code or just push the files directly.\n\n**4. The ICI London research grant (deadline 19 July 2026)** — from the Birmingham Odoo show session, Jemima is a strong co-applicant alongside you for the €1,500 Italian Cultural Institute grant. That draft WhatsApp message to Annavittoria Sarli was prepared — did you send it? If yes and she responded positively, the application is ready to write now.\n\n---\n\nWhat do you want to tackle first — fix the schema (step 1), or shall I write the Next.js frontend files you can push straight to GitHub?\n\ncan u pls sort this out and do so whilst i see it on a terminal, thanks.",
