    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Good. Now let me write the schema types. Based on the schema dump I saw earlier, here are the types that existed:\n\n1. `gherkinFeature` - seems like this might be from another project context, but it's in the schema\n2. `meetingSession` - also present\n3. `adrLog` - architecture decision record\n4. `scratchpadNote` - scratchpad notes\n5. `section` - portal section\n6. `portalConfig` - portal configuration\n7. `assetCard` - asset card (the one with the duplicate media field)\n8. `glossaryEntry` - glossary entries\n\nAnd the user wants to add:\n- `designTokens`\n- `referenceFile`\n\nLet me now write proper Sanity schema files. I'll split them into separate files for cleanliness.\n\nThe `assetCard` fix: The issue was a duplicate `media` field. Looking at the schema I read, the `image` field in `assetCard` had a nested `media` field. I think the issue was that there was both a top-level `media` field AND a nested one inside the image. Let me just write a clean `assetCard` without the duplicate.\n\nLet me write the schemas now.",
      "timestamp": 1781595801432
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\opencode\\\\sanity-work\\\\schemaTypes\\\\portalConfig.ts\", \"content\": \"import {defineType, defineField} from 'sanity'\\n\\nexport default defineType({\\n  name: 'portalConfig',\\n  title: 'Portal Configuration',\\n  type: 'document',\\n  fields: [\\n    defineField({name: 'browserTabTitle', type: 'string', title: 'Browser Tab Title', description: 'Appears in the browser tab and bookmarks'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'metaDescription', type: 'text', title: 'Meta Description', description: 'SEO description for the portal'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'favicon', type: 'image', title: 'Favicon', description: 'Browser tab icon', options: {hotspot: false}}),\\n    defineField({name: 'topBannerText', type: 'string', title: 'Top Banner Text', description: 'The slim banner across the very top of the page'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'heroBadge', type: 'string', title: 'Hero Badge Text', description: 'e.g. andiekobbietech Solutions'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'heroScript', type: 'string', title: 'Hero Script Text', description: 'Italic script above the main title e.g. Benvenuti a Casa'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'heroTitle', type: 'string', title: 'Hero Title'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'heroTagline', type: 'string', title: 'Hero Tagline'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'docRef', type: 'string', title: 'Document Reference', description: 'e.g. AK-NID-001'}),\\n    defineField({\\n      name: 'metaItems', type: 'array', title: 'Hero Meta Items',\\n      of: [{type: 'object', fields: [\\n        {name: 'label', type: 'string', title: 'Label'},\\n        {name: 'value', type: 'string', title: 'Value'},\\n      ]}]\\n    }),\\n    defineField({name: 'meetingDateIcon', type: 'string', title: 'Meeting Date Icon (emoji)'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'meetingTimeIcon', type: 'string', title: 'Meeting Time Icon (emoji)'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'meetingPersonIcon', type: 'string', title: 'Meeting Person Icon (emoji)'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'footerLogo', type: 'image', title: 'Footer Logo', options: {hotspot: true}}),\\n    defineField({name: 'footerCompanyName', type: 'string', title: 'Footer Company Name'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'footerTagline', type: 'string', title: 'Footer Tagline'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'footerDescription', type: 'text', title: 'Footer Description'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'footerMetaTag', type: 'string', title: 'Footer Meta Tag'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'stickyBarLabel', type: 'string', title: 'Sticky Bar Label'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'exportButtonLabel', type: 'string', title: 'Export Button Label'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'portalName', type: 'string', title: 'Portal Name (legacy)'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'tagline', type: 'string', title: 'Tagline (legacy)'}),\\n    defineField({name: 'metadata', type: 'string', title: 'Metadata (legacy)'}),\\n  ],\\n})\\n\"}",
