      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now let me deploy the schema. I can use `sanity deploy` but that deploys the studio. I actually need to use `sanity schema deploy` to push the schema to the dataset.\n\nWait, in Sanity v6, the schema is deployed as part of the studio. When you run `sanity deploy`, it deploys the studio. But the schema is automatically synced when the studio is deployed.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully - in Sanity, the schema is defined in the studio code, and when the studio runs (either locally or deployed), it registers the schema types. But the schema stored in the API (`_.schemas.default`) is a system document that the CLI or API can update.\n\nLet me try `sanity schema deploy` to push the schema to the dataset.",
